This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it describes a geo-replicated transactional key-value store that uses multiple Paxos implementations optimized for different purposes. It may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) categories as it deals with storing and accessing data. Additionally, it may belong to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category as it discusses the implementation of a system, and the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as it mentions providing strong guarantees.
